  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The article \"Sample selection models for count data in R\" by Karol Wyszynski and Giampiero Marra showcases a significant academic footprint with 9 citations, indicating its relevancy in the field of computational statistics.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The research article authored by Karol Wyszynski and Giampiero Marra has made a notable impact within the academic community, particularly in the realms of computational statistics. With 9 citations since its publication, the work reflects its acceptance and utilization by peers, underscoring the relevance of sample selection models for count data in the R programming language.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The geographical reach of this research is supported by its citations from various countries, including the United Kingdom, Italy, and the Netherlands, each contributing to a diversified discourse around the methods discussed in the paper. Such international attention hints at a wider applicability of the methodologies beyond local or niche contexts, suggesting that the findings resonate with a global audience.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Additionally, the article has been recognized in other scholarly venues, including \"Computational Statistics & Data Analysis\" and \"Socio-Economic Planning Sciences,\" indicating that it is being referenced in studies across different domains. Such citations suggest a robust dialogue around the statistical approaches to count data, affirming the foundational importance of the authors' contributions.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Furthermore, it is noteworthy that there have been 9 proven downstream reuse instances of the materials and methods developed in this article. This suggests a solid commitment to ongoing research in this area, where the tools and models proposed have been effectively integrated into subsequent scholarly work, enhancing methodological rigor in future studies.</p>",
